<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Last Updated: August 09, 2025</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[Company Name] ("we," "us," or "our") operates the [Website Name] website (the "Service"), a URL shortener service that allows users to create shortened URLs and QR codes. We may collect payments for premium features through Stripe. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website or use our Service, including data collected from clicks on shortened URLs.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not access the Service.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We collect information that identifies, relates to, describes, or is capable of being associated with you ("Personal Information"), as well as non-personal information. The types of information we collect depend on how you interact with the Service.</p>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl">a. Information You Provide Directly</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Account Information</strong>: When you create an account, we may collect your name, email address, password, and other registration details.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Payment Information</strong>: If you subscribe to paid features, we use Stripe to process payments. We do not store your credit card details; instead, Stripe handles payment processing and may collect billing information such as your name, email, billing address, and payment method details. Please review Stripe's Privacy Policy at <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">https://stripe.com/privacy</a> for more information.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Content You Submit</strong>: When you create shortened URLs or QR codes, we collect the original URL, any custom aliases, and associated metadata (e.g., descriptions or tags).</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl">b. Information Collected Automatically</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Usage and Device Information</strong>: When you access the Service, we automatically collect information about your device, including IP address, browser type, operating system, language preferences, screen resolution, and device type (e.g., mobile or desktop).</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Click Tracking Data</strong>: For shortened URLs and QR codes, we track interactions such as clicks or scans. This includes:
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">IP address</li>
<li class="break-words">Country and city (derived from IP address)</li>
<li class="break-words">Referrer (the website or source from which the click originated)</li>
<li class="break-words">Device type</li>
<li class="break-words">Browser type and version</li>
<li class="break-words">Language</li>
<li class="break-words">Operating system</li>
<li class="break-words">Screen resolution</li>
<li class="break-words">Date and time of the interaction</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Log Data</strong>: We collect server logs that may include your IP address, access times, pages viewed, and any errors encountered.</li>
</ul>
<h3 dir="auto" class="text-xl">c. Information from Third Parties</h3>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">We may receive information from third-party services, such as analytics providers or social media platforms, if you integrate them with our Service.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We do not knowingly collect sensitive personal information, such as racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, religious beliefs, or health data, unless you voluntarily provide it.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">2. How We Collect Information</h2>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Directly from You</strong>: Through forms, account creation, or communications with us.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Automatically</strong>: Using cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies (see Section 7 for details).</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">From Third Parties</strong>: Such as payment processors (e.g., Stripe) or analytics tools.</li>
</ul>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We use the information we collect for the following purposes:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words">To provide and maintain the Service, including creating shortened URLs, generating QR codes, and tracking clicks for analytics.</li>
<li class="break-words">To process payments and manage subscriptions via Stripe.</li>
<li class="break-words">To improve the Service, analyze usage trends, and develop new features.</li>
<li class="break-words">To communicate with you, such as sending service updates, newsletters, or responding to inquiries.</li>
<li class="break-words">To detect, prevent, and address fraud, security issues, or technical problems.</li>
<li class="break-words">To comply with legal obligations, enforce our terms, or protect our rights.</li>
<li class="break-words">For marketing purposes, such as promoting our services (you may opt out at any time).</li>
<li class="break-words">To generate aggregated, anonymized statistics that do not identify individuals.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Click tracking data is used to provide users with insights into link performance and to enhance service reliability.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">4. Sharing of Your Information</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We do not sell your Personal Information. We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">With Service Providers</strong>: We share information with third-party vendors, such as Stripe for payments, hosting providers, analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics), and email services, to perform functions on our behalf.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">For Business Transfers</strong>: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">For Legal Reasons</strong>: We may disclose information to comply with laws, respond to subpoenas, or protect the rights, property, or safety of us, our users, or others.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">With Your Consent</strong>: We may share information for any other purpose with your explicit consent.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Aggregated or anonymized data may be shared with partners for research or marketing.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">5. Data Security</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration. For example, we use encryption for data in transit and access controls. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Click tracking data is stored securely and used only for legitimate purposes outlined in this policy.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Depending on your location, you may have certain rights regarding your Personal Information:</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Access</strong>: Request details about the information we hold about you.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Correction</strong>: Update inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Deletion</strong>: Request deletion of your information, subject to legal exceptions (e.g., we may retain data for click tracking to maintain service integrity).</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Opt-Out</strong>: Unsubscribe from marketing communications or object to certain processing.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Portability</strong>: Receive a copy of your data in a structured format.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</strong>: You have the right to know, delete, correct, and opt out of the sale or sharing of your Personal Information. We do not sell Personal Information.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">EU/UK Residents (GDPR/UK GDPR)</strong>: You have rights to access, rectification, erasure, restriction, objection, and portability. You may also complain to a supervisory authority.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">To exercise these rights, contact us at [contact email, e.g., privacy@@[domain].com]. We may verify your identity before responding. Responses will be provided within applicable legal timeframes.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You can manage your account settings to update or delete information. For click tracking, note that data is often anonymized and not directly linked to individuals.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">We use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to collect information about your interactions with the Service. These help with functionality, analytics, and personalization.</p>
<ul dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Essential Cookies</strong>: Necessary for the Service to function.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Analytics Cookies</strong>: Track usage to improve the Service (e.g., Google Analytics).</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong class="font-semibold">Marketing Cookies</strong>: Used for targeted advertising.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">You can manage cookie preferences through your browser settings or by opting out via tools like the Network Advertising Initiative<a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow"></a>. For click tracking on shortened URLs, we may use these technologies to collect device and interaction data.</p>
<h2 dir="auto" class="text-2xl mt-[1.5em]">8. International Data Transfers</h2>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">If you are located outside the United States, your information may be transferred to and processed in the U.S. or other countries where our servers or service providers are located. We ensure appropriate safeguards, such as Standard Contractual Clauses, to protect your data in compliance with applicable laws like GDPR.</p>
